    "definingSkill": {
      "skillName": "Patch Job",
      "stat": "cra",
      "definition": "<p>A skilled craftsman can patch a weapon or armor well enough to keep it working and keep its wearer/wielder in the fight, whether that be by tying a bowstring back together, sharpening the edge of a broken blade, or nailing a plate over a cracked shield. By taking a turn to roll Patch Job at a DC equal to the item&rsquo;s Crafting DC-3 a Craftsman can restore a broken shield or armor to half its full SP or restore a broken weapon to half its durability. Until fixed at a forge, a patched weapon does half its normal damage.</p>\n<p>A weapon, shield, or armor&nbsp;which has already been&nbsp;patched once can only be&nbsp;patched again 1 more time,&nbsp;and this patch only brings it to&nbsp;1/4th SP/Reliability (rounding&nbsp;down).</p>",
