      "skill2": {
        "skillName": "Silver Coating",
        "stat": "cra",
        "definition": "<p>A Craftsman can coat an existing weapon in silver with a forge and a number of units of silver ingots based on the size of the weapon. The DC for this roll is 16. If you succeed, you may choose to add +1d6 silver damage to a weapon per 3 points you rolled above the DC, up to 5d6. On succes, the Silver Damage is subtracted by the base damage of the weapon (minimum 1d6). Failing the roll breaks the weapon.</p>\n<p>Silver coating requires 2 ingots&nbsp;of silver for 1-handed&nbsp;weapons, 4 ingots of silver for&nbsp;2-handed weapons, and 1 ingot&nbsp;of silver for up to 10 arrows&nbsp;or crossbow bolts.</p>",
